Service Engineer (MS/201310/01/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00005580
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Oct 14 2013
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Carry out surveys / start-ups / troubleshooting independently onboard vessels / barges / rigs and provide timely and accurate reports as per the required standards.
Provide marine technical support and pre-sales and post-sales technical support remotely / on-site, as required.
Read and interpret hydraulic and electrical circuit diagrams and carry out troubleshooting, commissioning, terminations/tests as required.
Take responsibility of effectively communicating with customers.
Requirements:
Degree or Diploma in Engineering in Marine, Mechanical, Electronics/Electrical with 2 or more years of service experience in process industry, marine or oil and gas industry.
Technical and detail oriented.
Must be willing to travel in the Asia Pacific region and work in odd hours with advance notice.
Must be aware of the safety rules in the marine industry.
Familiarity with marine working environment will be an advantage; able to spend 2 to 3 days onboard vessels/barges, if required.